# RealtimePanel — Cline AI Rules

## Project Identity
Self-hosted WebSocket management dashboard for Soketi (Pusher-protocol-compatible). Backend: PHP 8.3 / Laravel 12. Frontend: React 19 pure SPA. Infra: MySQL 8, Redis 7, Soketi, Nginx, Docker Compose.

---

## Absolute Rules (Never Violate)

- Always run `php artisan pint` before committing PHP code
- Always write a PHPUnit Feature test for every new API endpoint
- Never add `$fillable` or `$guarded` to models — `Model::unguard()` is global in AppServiceProvider
- Never modify `vendor/`, `bootstrap/cache/`, or `public/build/`
- Never use Livewire or Alpine.js — frontend is a pure React SPA
- Never add logic to Blade templates — `resources/views/app.blade.php` is only the SPA root shell

---

## Backend: File Locations

- API controllers → `app/Http/Controllers/Api/`
- Models → `app/Models/` (Application.php, User.php)
- Services → `app/Services/` (PusherService.php, WebSocket/SoketiDriver.php)
- Traits → `app/Traits/HasOwnership.php`
- Contracts → `app/Contracts/WebSocketServerContract.php`
- Routes → `routes/api.php`
- Migrations → `database/migrations/`

---

## Backend: Authorization — Two Patterns (Critical)

### CRUD resource controllers → 403 on violation
```php
private function authorizeOwnership(Application $application): void
{
    if (auth()->user()->is_admin) return;
    if ($application->created_by !== auth()->id()) abort(403);
}
```
Use this pattern in resource (CRUD) controllers only.

### Event/trigger controllers → 404 on violation
```php
$app = Application::ownershipAware()
    ->where('enabled', true)
    ->findOrFail($validated['application_id']);
```
Use this pattern in any new event-trigger endpoint (Chat, Chess, TienLen style).

The base `Controller` class has NO `authorizeOwnership` method. Do not invent one.

---

## Backend: Every Trigger Must Dual-Broadcast

```php
$pusher->trigger($channel, $eventName, $data);
$pusher->trigger('_monitor_' . $app->id, 'monitor.event', [
    'channel' => $channel,
    'event'   => $eventName,
    'data'    => $data,
]);
```

---

## Backend: After Any Application Update

```php
$application->update($data);
$application->clearCache(); // deletes soketi_app:{key} from Redis — required
```

---

## Backend: Migration Pattern

```php
Schema::create('table_name', function (Blueprint $table) {
    $table->id();
    // ... columns ...
    $table->ownerships(); // macro: adds created_by + updated_by (nullable FK + index)
    $table->timestamps();
});
```

---

## Backend: Route Registration Order

Always declare custom/named routes BEFORE `apiResource()`:

```php
Route::get('/applications/stats', [ApplicationController::class, 'stats']);
Route::get('/applications/{application}/channels', [...]);
Route::patch('/applications/{application}/toggle', [...]);
Route::apiResource('/applications', ApplicationController::class); // LAST
```

---

## Backend: `POST /applications` Intentional Rule

`store()` validates only `name` + `enabled`. Limit fields are SET only via `update()` (PUT). Do not add limit fields to `store()`.

---

## Backend: New Endpoint Checklist

1. Controller in `app/Http/Controllers/Api/`
2. Route inside `Route::middleware('auth:sanctum')->group(...)` in `routes/api.php`
3. Named routes before `apiResource()` calls
4. Correct ownership pattern (resource=403, trigger=404)
5. `response()->json(['ok' => true])` for operations; full model for CRUD
6. `$application->clearCache()` after any Application modification

---

## Frontend: File Locations

- Pages → `resources/js/pages/<section>/`
- Layout → `resources/js/components/layout/AppLayout`
- UI components → `resources/js/components/ui/` (shadcn/ui)
- API client → `resources/js/lib/axios.js`
- Echo factory → `resources/js/lib/echo.js`
- Router → `resources/js/router.jsx`
- Hooks → `resources/js/hooks/` (useAuth, useTheme, useToast)

---

## Frontend: API Import (Always This Exact Import)

```js
import api from '@/lib/axios'
```

Never use `@/lib/api`. The file is `axios.js`. It auto-attaches Bearer token from localStorage and redirects to `/login` on 401.

---

## Frontend: Adding a New Route

```jsx
// 1. Create page: resources/js/pages/section/MyPage.jsx
// 2. In router.jsx, add:
const myRoute = createRoute({
    getParentRoute: () => rootRoute,
    path: '/my-path',
    component: MyPage,
    beforeLoad: requireAuth, // required for all protected routes
});
// 3. Add myRoute to routeTree.addChildren([..., myRoute])
```

---

## Frontend: Query and Mutation Pattern

```jsx
const { data, isLoading } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['key', param],
    queryFn: () => api.get('/endpoint').then(r => r.data),
});

const mutation = useMutation({
    mutationFn: (payload) => api.post('/endpoint', payload),
    onSuccess: () => {
        queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['key'] });
        toast({ title: 'Done!', variant: 'success' });
    },
    onError: (err) => {
        if (err.response?.status === 422) setErrors(err.response.data.errors ?? {});
    },
});
```

---

## Testing: New Test File Template

```php
<?php

namespace Tests\Feature\Section;

use App\Models\Application;
use App\Models\User;
use App\Services\PusherService;
use Illuminate\Foundation\Testing\RefreshDatabase;
use Mockery\MockInterface;
use Pusher\Pusher;
use Tests\TestCase;

class MyTest extends TestCase
{
    use RefreshDatabase;

    private function mockPusher(): void
    {
        $pusher = $this->createMock(Pusher::class);
        $pusher->method('trigger')->willReturn((object) []);

        $this->mock(PusherService::class, function (MockInterface $mock) use ($pusher) {
            $mock->shouldReceive('make')->andReturn($pusher);
        });
    }

    // Required test cases per endpoint:
    // - test_owner_can_use_endpoint
    // - test_non_owner_gets_404 (trigger) OR test_non_owner_gets_403 (resource)
    // - test_disabled_app_returns_404
    // - test_unauthenticated_gets_401
    // - test_validation_fails_with_missing_fields
}
```

### Cache spy for update/toggle tests

```php
use Tests\Concerns\MocksWebSocketServer;

class MyTest extends TestCase
{
    use RefreshDatabase, MocksWebSocketServer;

    public function test_update_clears_cache(): void
    {
        $spy = $this->spyWebSocketServer();
        // ... perform update request ...
        $this->assertCacheClearedFor($app, $spy);
    }
}
```

Factory states: `Application::factory()->disabled()`, `User::factory()->inactive()`

---

## Commands

```bash
docker compose up -d        # start all services
php artisan pint             # code style — run before every PHP commit
php artisan test             # PHPUnit tests
php artisan migrate          # run pending migrations
php artisan optimize:clear   # clear all Laravel caches
npm run dev                  # Vite dev server (hot reload)
npm run build                # production build → public/build/
npm run test                 # Vitest
npx playwright test          # E2E tests
```

---

## Key Facts to Remember

- Soketi caches app config in Redis DB 0 under `soketi_app:{key}` AND `soketi_app:{id}`. `clearCache()` deletes both.
- Laravel app cache lives in Redis DB 1. Game rooms stored there as `chess_room_{code}` / `tienlen_room_{code}`.
- `is_admin` boolean on `users` — no spatie/laravel-permission installed.
- Admin sees all applications. Non-admin only sees `created_by = auth()->id()` via `ownershipAware()` scope.
- Default dev credentials: `admin@email.com` / `password`
- `POST /applications` does NOT save limit fields (only `name` + `enabled`). This is intentional.
- `_monitor_{appId}` channel receives copies of all events for the live Monitor page.
